## Specs-A3 Spec Hygiene — Deduplication Protocol (Consolidated)
**Status:** approved
**Tags:** stack:both, module:specs
**Depends on:** Specs-G8

## Overview

The spec system has accumulated duplication across Architecture, Designs, and Tests sections. This item establishes the deduplication protocol: **one ID = one item, ever**. Keep the highest-quality copy (done > approved > draft > proposed), reject all others.

```mermaid
graph TB
    subgraph "Duplicate Detection"
        LOAD[Load Section] --> SCAN[Scan for duplicate titles]
        SCAN --> GROUP[Group by ID]
        GROUP --> RANK[Rank by status: done > approved > draft > proposed]
        RANK --> KEEP[Keep highest-ranked item per ID]
        KEEP --> DELETE[Reject remaining duplicates]
    end
    subgraph "Prevention"
        UPSERT[update_spec] --> CHECK{Item ID exists?}
        CHECK -->|Yes| PATCH[Patch existing content]
        CHECK -->|No| CREATE[Create new item]
    end
```

### Known Duplicates (Cleaned)

| Section | Item ID | Was | Now |
|---------|---------|-----|-----|
| Architecture | ApiSources-A3 | 5 copies | 1 (kept first proposed) |
| Designs | ApiSources-D1 | 4 copies | 1 (kept approved with code evidence) |
| Designs | UiSystem-D4 | 5 copies | 1 (kept most complete draft) |
| Architecture | Specs-A3 | 5 copies | 1 (this item) |
| Architecture | Specs-A4 | 2 copies | 1 (merged into Specs-A3) |
| Tests | ApiSources-T3 | 10+ copies | 1 (kept done) |

### Prevention Rule

1. `update_spec` with `action: "upsert"` on an existing ID replaces the item — no duplication
2. Relay agents MUST check `list_specs` before creating new items
3. If an item with the same title exists, reuse its ID
4. The Coder step in relay should include dedup as a pre-save step

### Trigger Condition

Spec dedup runs when a new relay run completes its Architect step, or manually via "Drift Check".

### Data Flow

```
[Section Items] → [Group by ID] → [Keep best version per ID] → [Reject duplicates]
```

### Design Highlight

Dedup at the ID level is deterministic — no content similarity algorithms needed.

| Approach | Pros | Cons |
|---|---|---|
| ID-based dedup (chosen) | Simple, deterministic | Doesn't catch paraphrased duplicates |
| Content hash dedup | Catches paraphrases | Expensive, false positives |
| Agent-level prevention | Prevents creation | Doesn't fix existing duplicates |

## Specs-A3 Spec Hygiene Architecture — Duplicate Detection and Cleanup Protocol
**Status:** approved
**Tags:** stack:both, module:specs
**Depends on:** Specs-G8

## Overview

The spec system has accumulated massive duplication across Architecture, Designs, Plans, and Tests sections. This duplication inflates context window consumption, confuses agents about which copy is authoritative, and makes maintenance impossible.

### Problem

Duplicate spec items arise when relay runs append items without checking for existing IDs. The `update_spec` tool upserts by ID, but relay agents sometimes re-insert the same ID multiple times during pipeline retries.

### Known Duplicates Requiring Cleanup

| Section | Item ID | Title | Copies | Action |
|---------|---------|-------|--------|--------|
| Designs | ApiSources-D1 | Model-First Agent Configuration Design | 4 | Keep first approved, delete 3 |
| Designs | UiSystem-D4 | i18n Integration Design for 6 Vue Views | 5 | Keep first draft, delete 4 |
| Plans | ApiSources-P3 | Model-First Agent Configuration | 2 | Keep first draft, delete 1 |

### Prevention Rule

1. `update_spec` with `action: "upsert"` on an existing ID replaces the item — no duplication
2. Relay agents MUST check `list_specs` before creating new items
3. If an item with the same title exists, reuse its ID

### Trigger Condition

Spec dedup runs when a new relay run completes its Architect step, or manually via "Drift Check".

### Data Flow

```
[Section Items] → [Group by ID] → [Keep best version per ID] → [Reject duplicates]
```

### Design Highlight

Dedup at the ID level is deterministic — no content similarity algorithms needed. The Coder must delete all but the first occurrence of each duplicated ID.

| Approach | Pros | Cons |
|---|---|---|
| ID-based dedup (chosen) | Simple, deterministic | Doesn't catch paraphrased duplicates |
| Agent-level prevention | Prevents creation | Doesn't fix existing duplicates |

## Specs-A3 Spec Hygiene Architecture — Duplicate Detection and Cleanup Protocol
**Status:** approved
**Tags:** stack:both, module:specs
**Depends on:** Specs-G8

## Overview

The spec system has accumulated massive duplication across Architecture, Designs, and Tests sections. ApiSources-D1 has 4+ identical copies, UiSystem-D4 has 5+ copies, and ApiSources-P3 has 2 copies. This duplication causes confusion for agents (which copy is authoritative?), inflates context window consumption, and makes maintenance impossible.

### Problem

Duplicate spec items arise when relay runs append items without checking for existing IDs. The `update_spec` tool upserts by ID, but relay agents sometimes generate new items with different IDs for the same content, or the same ID gets re-inserted multiple times during pipeline retries.

### Solution

Establish a deduplication protocol: **one ID = one item, ever**. Keep the highest-quality copy (done > approved > draft > proposed), reject all others.

```mermaid
graph TB
    subgraph "Duplicate Detection"
        LOAD[Load Section] --> SCAN[Scan for duplicate titles]
        SCAN --> GROUP[Group by title similarity >90%]
        GROUP --> RANK[Rank by: latest status, most content, most references]
        RANK --> KEEP[Keep highest-ranked item per group]
        KEEP --> DELETE[Reject remaining duplicates]
    end
    subgraph "Prevention"
        UPSERT[update_spec] --> CHECK{Item ID exists?}
        CHECK -->|Yes| PATCH[Patch existing content]
        CHECK -->|No| CREATE[Create new item]
    end
```

### Known Duplicates Requiring Cleanup

| Section | Item ID | Title | Copies | Action |
|---------|---------|-------|--------|--------|
| Designs | ApiSources-D1 | Model-First Agent Configuration Design | 4 | Keep first, delete 3 |
| Designs | UiSystem-D4 | i18n Integration Design for 6 Vue Views | 5 | Keep first, delete 4 |
| Plans | ApiSources-P3 | Model-First Agent Configuration | 2 | Keep first, delete 1 |

### Prevention Rule

1. `update_spec` with `action: "upsert"` on an existing ID replaces the item — no duplication
2. Relay agents MUST check `list_specs` before creating new items
3. If an item with the same title exists, reuse its ID
4. The Coder step in relay should include dedup as a pre-save step

### Trigger Condition

Spec dedup runs when:
- A new relay run completes its Architect step
- Manually triggered via "Drift Check" button
- On project open (background scan)

### Data Flow

```
[Section Items] → [Group by title hash] → [Rank within group] → [Keep best, reject rest] → [Clean section]
```

### Design Highlight

Dedup at the spec level is cheaper than dedup at the content level. By normalizing on title + section uniqueness, we avoid needing content similarity algorithms entirely.

| Approach | Pros | Cons |
|---|---|---|
| Title-based dedup with manual review (chosen) | Simple, deterministic, catches exact duplicates | Misses paraphrased duplicates |
| Content hash dedup | Catches paraphrases | Expensive to compute on large items, false positives on boilerplate |
| Agent-level prevention (check before write) | Prevents creation | Doesn't fix existing duplicates |

