## Specs-A4 Spec Duplication Diagnostic & Root Cause Analysis
**Status:** approved
**Tags:** stack:both, module:specs, type:diagnostic
**Depends on:** Specs-A3, Specs-G8

## Spec Duplication Diagnostic & Root Cause Analysis

### Problem

The test specs section contains **massive duplication**. `ApiSources-T3` has **10+ copies** with statuses ranging from `draft` to `done`. `ApiSources-D1` has **5+ copies** in designs. This is the root cause of "debug test" failures — agents read conflicting versions of the same test spec and produce inconsistent implementations.

### Root Cause

The `update_spec` tool upserts by `item_id`, but relay pipeline retries and re-runs create new items with the same ID. Each relay run appends items without checking for existing IDs. The pipeline's retry loop (Tester→Coder) exacerbates this by regenerating test specs on each iteration.

### Current Duplication Inventory

| Section | Item ID | Copies | Statuses | Action |
|---------|---------|--------|----------|--------|
| tests | ApiSources-T3 | **10+** | draft, done, proposed | Keep ONE done copy, delete rest |
| designs | ApiSources-D1 | **5+** | proposed, approved | Keep ONE approved copy, delete rest |
| designs | UiSystem-D4 | **5+** | draft | Keep ONE most complete copy |
| architecture | ApiSources-A3 | **5+** | proposed | Keep ONE, delete rest |
| goals | Specs-G8/Specs-G9 | 2 | proposed | Keep Specs-G8, reject Specs-G9 |

### Data Flow — How Duplicates Are Created

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant R1 as Relay Run 1
    participant R2 as Relay Run 2
    participant R3 as Relay Run 3 (retry)
    participant Specs as Specs Store

    R1->>Specs: update_spec("ApiSources-T3", draft)
    Note over Specs: T3 created (draft)
    R2->>Specs: update_spec("ApiSources-T3", draft)
    Note over Specs: T3 upserted → BUT relay appends if step regenerates
    R3->>Specs: update_spec("ApiSources-T3", done)
    Note over Specs: Another T3 appended (done)
    Note over Specs: Result: 3+ copies of T3
```

### Fix Strategy

1. **Immediate**: Delete all duplicate items, keeping highest-quality copy per ID
2. **Prevention**: The `update_spec` tool already upserts by ID — duplicates only appear when relay retries regenerate items. The fix is in the relay driver: check `list_specs` before creating test items.

### Impact on "Debug Test"

When a relay run hits the Tester step, the Tester reads `ApiSources-T3` and sees 10+ conflicting versions. This causes:
- Confusion about which test cases are authoritative
- Wasted context window tokens reading duplicate content
- Potential for writing tests against the wrong spec version
- Test verification failures when implementation matches one copy but Tester reads another

### Resolution

Deduplicate by keeping the highest-status copy:
1. `done` > `approved` > `implemented` > `in_progress` > `draft` > `proposed` > `empty`
2. If tied, keep the copy with the most content
3. Delete all other copies

### Design Highlight

This is not a code bug — it's a spec hygiene issue. The fix is deduplication of existing specs plus a prevention rule in the relay driver. No code changes needed for the immediate fix; only spec cleanup.

## Specs-A5 Spec Deduplication & Hygiene — Root Cause and Resolution Architecture
**Status:** approved
**Tags:** stack:both, module:specs
**Depends on:** Specs-G8, Specs-G9

## Spec Deduplication & Hygiene Architecture — Root Cause and Resolution


### Problem

The spec system has accumulated massive duplication across Architecture, Designs, and Tests sections. `ApiSources-D1` has **5+ identical copies**, `UiSystem-D4` has **6+ copies**, `ApiSources-A3` has **5+ copies**, and `ApiSources-T3` has **10+ copies**. This duplication causes:

1. **Agent confusion**: Relay agents read conflicting versions of the same spec
2. **Context waste**: Duplicate items inflate context window consumption
3. **Maintenance impossibility**: No way to determine which copy is authoritative

### Root Cause

The `update_spec` tool correctly upserts by `item_id`, but relay pipeline retries and re-runs create new items with the same ID by appending rather than replacing. The pipeline's Tester→Coder retry loop exacerbates this by regenerating test specs on each iteration.

### Solution Architecture

```mermaid
graph TB
    subgraph "Detection"
        LOAD[Load Section Items] --> GROUP[Group by item_id]
        GROUP --> RANK[Rank: done > approved > draft > proposed]
        RANK --> SELECT[Select highest-ranked per ID]
    end
    subgraph "Resolution"
        SELECT --> KEEP[Keep ONE item per ID]
        KEEP --> REJECT[Mark duplicates as rejected]
    end
    subgraph "Prevention"
        UPSERT[update_spec call] --> CHECK{Item exists?}
        CHECK -->|Yes| REPLACE[Replace content in-place]
        CHECK -->|No| CREATE[Create new item]
    end
```

### Selection Algorithm

```
statusRank = { done:10, verified:9, implemented:8, approved:7,
               in_review:6, in_progress:5, stable:4,
               draft:3, proposed:2, backlog:1, empty:0 }

selectBestCopy(items[]):
  return items.sortBy((a, b) =>
    statusRank[b.status] - statusRank[a.status]
    || b.content.length - a.content.length
  )[0]
```

### Trigger Condition

Dedup runs when:
- A new relay run completes its Architect step
- Manually triggered via "Drift Check" button
- On project open (background scan)

### Data Flow

```
[Section Items] → [Group by item_id] → [Rank within group by status + content length]
  → [Keep highest-ranked item] → [Reject remaining duplicates] → [Save clean section]
```

### Duplicate Inventory (Current)

| Section | Item ID | Copies | Action |
|---------|---------|--------|--------|
| architecture | Specs-A3 | 4 | Keep first approved, reject 3 |
| architecture | ApiSources-A3 | 5 | Keep first, reject 4 |
| designs | ApiSources-D1 | 5 | Keep first approved, reject 4 |
| designs | UiSystem-D4 | 6 | Keep first draft, reject 5 |
| designs | Specs-D13 | 2 | Keep first, reject 1 |
| tests | ApiSources-T3 | 10+ | Keep "done" copy, reject 9+ |
| goals | Specs-G8/Specs-G9 | 2 | Keep G8, reject G9 |

### Design Highlight

Dedup at the `item_id` level is deterministic — no content similarity algorithms needed. One ID = one item, ever. The Coder step in relay must call `update_spec(action: "upsert")` rather than appending new items.

| Approach | Pros | Cons |
|---|---|---|
| **ID-based dedup with status ranking** (chosen) | Simple, deterministic, preserves audit trail via rejected status | Does not catch paraphrased duplicates with different IDs |
| Content hash dedup | Catches paraphrases | Expensive, false positives on boilerplate |
| Agent-level prevention only | Prevents creation | Does not fix existing duplicates |

### Quality Checklist

- [x] Mermaid structural diagram included
- [x] Trigger condition documented
- [x] Data flow documented
- [x] Trade-offs table with ≥2 alternatives
- [x] No unhandled error cases (all duplicates have defined action)
- [x] Explicit data lifecycle (reject → audit trail preserved)
